# Windsurf Rules — AETHER_02

## Project Identity

AETHER_02 — Linux MCP server, 12 tools, 99.9% system management.
- **Language:** Rust (edition 2021, nightly toolchain for hardening flags)
- **Target:** Linux x86-64/arm64
- **Transport:** stdio — stdout is JSON-RPC exclusively

## Build

```bash
cargo check
cargo build
cargo test
cargo clippy -- -D warnings
cargo fmt --check
```

## Architecture

```
src/
├── main.rs      — tokio::main, dotenvy, tracing→stderr, serve((stdin,stdout))
├── server.rs    — AetherServer, tool_router, tool_handler, ActionParams
├── config.rs    — FeatureGates from .env
├── error.rs     — AetherError + POSIX/nix error helpers
├── audit.rs     — log_success, log_failure, log_forced, log_security
└── tools/
    ├── process.rs     — 1. process_control
    ├── filesystem.rs  — 2. file_system
    ├── packages.rs    — 3. package_manager
    ├── sysconfig.rs   — 4. system_config
    ├── service.rs     — 5. service_manager
    ├── gui.rs         — 6. gui_automation
    ├── sysinfo.rs     — 7. system_info
    ├── network.rs     — 8. network_manager
    ├── user.rs        — 9. user_management
    ├── security.rs    — 10. security_audit
    ├── hardware.rs    — 11. hardware_control
    └── automation.rs  — 12. system_automation
```

## Key Rules

### NEVER
- Print to stdout (MCP JSON-RPC channel)
- Use `bash -c`, `sh -c`, `system()`, or interpolated shell commands for tool operations
- Modify `mcp.json` or `.env` without explicit user request
- Skip `// SAFETY:` comments on unsafe blocks
- Enable destructive feature gates by default

### ALWAYS
- Validate all tool parameters before syscalls or CLI invocations
- Check `force: true` for destructive operations
- Check feature gates for privileged kernel/system operations
- Pass CLI args as `Command::new(...).args([...])`, never shell strings
- Canonicalize file paths before filesystem operations
- Audit-log every tool invocation to stderr
- Use `Result<T, AetherError>` for tool internals

## Adding Actions

```rust
"new_action" => {
    let ctx = ErrorContext::new("tool_name", "new_action");
    let p = get_string_param(params, "required_param", &ctx)?;

    if !require_force(params) {
        return Err(AetherError::force_required(ctx));
    }

    audit::log_success("tool_name", "new_action", &format!("param={p}"));
    Ok(serde_json::json!({ "ok": true }).to_string())
}
```

## Feature Gates

```rust
server.gates.check(ctx, server.gates.module_load, "AETHER_MODULE_LOAD")?;
```

Eight gates, all off by default: `KEXEC_LOAD`, `MODULE_LOAD`, `BPF_LOAD`, `PTRACE_ATTACH`, `NAMESPACE_CREATE`, `OFFLINE_MOUNT`, `PARTITION_EDIT`, `TOKEN_MANIPULATION`.
